<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1"?>
<pattern xmlns="http://docs.javascribe.com/pattern"
xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
xsi:schemaLocation="http://docs.javascribe.com/pattern ../../pattern.xsd"
name="Classification" id="Classification" priority="12500"
namespace="http://javascribe.sf.net/patterns/classification"
xmlElement="classification">

<description>
<p>
A classification is a Java interface with getter and setter functions for a set of attributes, and it 
represents a set of attributes that form an abstraction of data.  Classifications may extend one another 
and be used to create an abstract object hierarchy in the application's data model.
</p>
<p>
When all classifications are read, and entity manager(s) and data objects are read, classifications are 
applied to all JPA entities and data objects as appropriate.
</p>
</description>

